author: Tommy Stubbington
title: Global Stocks Climb Ahead of Fed Rate Decision
text:
Global stock markets climbed Wednesday as investors remained upbeat approaching the U.S. Federal Reserve decision on whether to raise interest rates for the first time in nearly a decade.
The Stoxx Europe 600 was 1.1% higher in early European trade, buoyed by Tuesday’s rally on Wall Street. Analysts said solid U.S. retail sales data on Tuesday helped spur the positive mood in markets, which continued into Wednesday’s session.
